State Farm Pays $1.75 Billion in Disaster Insurance Claims for May, April

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-06-16T22:23:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/state-farm-pays-1-75-billion-in-disaster-insurance-claims-for-may-april.html
     June 16 (Bloomberg) --State Farm Mutual Automobile
Insurance Co., the largest U.S. home and car insurer, said it
has paid almost $1.75 billion in claims from natural disasters
in April and May, including hailstorms and tornadoes.  Customers have reported more than 400,000 claims, according
to a PR Newswire statement today from the Bloomington, Illinois-
based insurer. State Farm is owned by policyholders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  